Government of Maharashtra

Martyr Rajguru Chowk, Madam Cama Marg,
Mantralaya, Mumbai 400032
Date: 26th of May, 2025

Preamble: The procedure for the award of cash and appropriation of the prize money to the winning local bodies in the 12 groups of Majhi Vasundhara Abhiyan 4.0 has been notified vide Government Decision dated 27.09.2024 at Reference No. Accordingly, a Detailed Project Report of the works to be taken up by the local bodies out of the award amount has been prepared vide Government Decision dated 08.02.2022 at Reference No. Administrative approval has to be obtained from a committee constituted under the chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment and Climate Change.

2. Accordingly, for grant of administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report received from the Awardee Local Bodies, Ms. The Committee has made recommendations after discussing the Detailed Project Report submitted by the Local Bodies in its meeting held on 02.05.2025 under the Chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment & Climate Change. It was under the consideration of the government to grant administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report of the respective local bodies as recommended by the committee.

Government Decision: Taking into consideration the points mentioned in the proposal, my ACN Mission 4. 0 will provide a total amount of Rs. The detailed project report of the cost of 2,25,00, 000.00 (Rupees Two Crore Twenty Five Lakhs only) has been submitted by the Village Development Officer, Ghulewadi Gram Panchayat with the technical approval of the Executive Engineer, Zilla Parishad Ahilyanagar. The proposal was submitted by the Ghulewadi Gram Panchayat. Secretary, Environment and Climate
Government Decision No: Mission-2024 / Q.No.04 / T.H.2, dated: 26th May, 2025

The date of the committee constituted under the chairmanship of the change department was taken into consideration in its meetings held on 02nd May, 2025. As per the recommendations of the committee, the total amount submitted by the Ghulewadi Gram Panchayat is Rs. The works in the Detailed Project Report costing 2,25,00, 000.00 (Rs.2 crore TAA attention only) are being accorded administrative sanction by the Government subject to the following conditions and conditions. The works for which administrative sanction is being granted are shown in the accompanying Annexure-9.
2. Terms and Conditions 1) The working mechanism for the works in this Detailed Project Report shall be the Ghulewadi Gram Panchayat.

2) The financial and physical progress report of the implementation of the works mentioned in this Detailed Project Report should be sent to my Vasundhara Mission Directorate by the 5th of every month.
3) The implementation of the works in this Detailed Project Report should be completed within the next 6 months from the date of administrative approval.
4) If the amount of the prize exceeds the amount, it should be made out of self-funding.
5) In case of any increase in the original project cost in this Detailed Project Report for any reason, no additional funds / grants will be made available for the same.

3. Under the Majhi Vasundhara Abhiyan, the Ghulewadi Gram Panchayat has received the "Gram Panchayat Group (population more than 10 thousand)" State-level second-highest prize of Rs. Out of the prize money of Rs. The first instalment of ₹1 crore has been disbursed to them. Since the detailed project report of the works to be taken out of this prize money has been granted administrative approval by the Government as per paragraph-1 above, the remaining amount of the prize money to the Ghulewadi Gram Panchayat is Rs. The government is approving the release of the second instalment of ₹11250 crore (₹1 crore 12 lakh 50 thousand only) through the Maharashtra Pollution Control Board.
